<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[96,698,1317,1467]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Males of this cryptically coloured species engage in prolonged ritual contests, something not seen in any other 
<taxonomicName box="[171,264,1379,1404]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[171,264,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Maratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<emphasis box="[352,577,1378,1404]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bat Peacock Spider</emphasis>
is widely distributed and is found in drier habitats or on gravel.
</paragraph>
